HEADWORD: Wattmeter
<hw>Watt"me`ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Watt</ets> +
<ets>meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for
measuring power in watts, -- much used in measuring the energy of an
electric current.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

